 The Zambian truck, which was carrying a full load of acid, lost control after break failure and jack-knifed into one of the barriers. The driver narrowly escaped with his life and fortunately, wasn’t seriously injured. The pass has been reduced to two single lanes to ease traffic build up. The truck will later be hauled out and motorists can expect the pass to be closed. •Usage of alternative routes is advised.    R10 000 reward for information ‘We should kill him’ – Truck driver hears how hijackers argue about his fate #TrafficUpdate: Avoid N4 near Machadodorp VIDEO: Machadodorp two granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za